CostTracker Unit Tests Implementation

WHY: CostTracker in internal/spending/costs.go had 0% test coverage for its key methods (GetDeploymentCosts, GetTotalMonthlySpend, GetCostsByDeployment, CheckAlerts, GetDeploymentsOverBudget, GenerateMonitoringReport). These methods are critical for enforcing spending safeguards.

WHAT CHANGED:
1. Added CostExplorerAPI interface to enable mocking the AWS Cost Explorer client
2. Added NewCostTrackerWithClient() constructor for dependency injection
3. Added NewCostMonitorWithTracker() for testing CostMonitor
4. Added 10 comprehensive test cases:
   - Success scenarios with mock responses
   - Error handling (API failures, invalid amounts)
   - Alert threshold detection
   - Budget exceeded detection

DESIGN DECISIONS:
- Interface extracts only GetCostAndUsage method (only Cost Explorer method used)
- Mock allows testing business logic without AWS credentials
- Tests verify:
  - Request parameters (tags, date ranges, grouping)
  - Response parsing (cost amounts, deployment grouping)
  - Alert threshold calculations
  - Budget utilization math

COVERAGE IMPACT:
- internal/spending package: 23.0% → 50.6%
- costs.go methods now have mock-based test coverage

REMAINING:
- CostMonitor lifecycle tests (Start/Stop/runLoop) - would need goroutine testing
- pricing.go EstimateCosts (requires Pricing API mock)
